<br>
You have the right to question why a post was deleted, you have the right to say how you feel about it, you have the right to say and do whatever you want, but it is within the administrators and moderators rights on this board to determine what is appropriate and what is not.<br>
<br>
Being an admistrator is very difficult, because we cannot please all the people all the time.  We get accused of favoritism left and right, we get accused of keeping people from their freedom of speech rights left and right, we get accused of having ulterior motives and being board nazi's and get threatened that another board will pop up and it'll be 100s times better than this one, yet we still stick with this board and do what we can to keep it running as smooth as possible.<br>
<br>
We respect your rights, your comments, the way you choose to play EQ, the way you choose to deal with things, but please respect the fact that we have to make decisions that are not always easy and take the flack for them from a group or group of people.<br>
<br>
Now that being said, I personally do not think that pointing out who's selling what, where, when, why and how when dealing with RL sales needs to be on this board.  I can say that anyone selling characters or items for RL money will be banned from this board if they post here for sales.  Go to another site for that kind of deal.<br>
<br>
As to the cursing issue, cursing is fine, we're all pretty grown up and its not like we haven't cursed ourselves, but there is a limit to what is approrpriate and what is not.<br>
<br>
